# Line-ending policy: force LF for the text the fleet is authored in, so the pure-stdlib Python
# validator and the readonly-guard.py hook (invoked via POSIX shell) read identical bytes on every
# OS. CRLF breaks POSIX-shell hooks and the line-oriented
# frontmatter parser (a trailing \r stops the `--- ` fence from matching).
*.md   text eol=lf
*.py   text eol=lf
*.sh   text eol=lf
*.ps1  text eol=lf
*.yml  text eol=lf
*.yaml text eol=lf
*.json text eol=lf
